		<div class="container" style="padding: 0 1rem">
			<h2 id="Age_Prediction">Bone2gene: Age Prediction</h2>
			<br>
			<div class="img">
				<%= image_tag("boneage.jpg") %>
			</div>
			<p style="text-align: justify">
				Growth disorder is one of the main symptoms of many skeletal diseases and radiologic bone age assessment is one
				of the important tools for their diagnosis. Our Bone2Gene classifier is built upon a deep convolutional neural
				network model that we trained on 12,000 X-rays from the Radiological Society of North America (RSNA).
				Our bone age model achieved a state-of-the-art precision of mean absolute difference of 4.2 months with respect
				to the average of seven human graders (on RSNA test date set), and only 7.5 months with respect to one human
				grader on our skeletal disorder dataset (despite their dysmorphic features).
			</p>
			<div id="DL" class="img">
				<%= image_tag("DL_vs_visual_Bone_Age.jpg") %>
			</div>
			<p>
				We will soon deploy our bone age model as a web-based tool for clinical use.
			</p>

